      "label": "synthesis",
      "phase": "Research",
      "prompt": "You are synthesizing research about the @quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows plugin for pi coding agent. Here are the research results:\n\n[\n  \"## Research Summary: `@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows` v2.9.0\\n\\n### What it does\\nDynamic workflow orchestration for Pi — fan tasks across subagents with real model routing, token accounting, resume, and interactive TUI. Claude Code-style, production-grade.\\n\\n### Config options\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|------|---------|\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/settings.json` | Global settings, custom `keywordTriggerWord` |\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/model-tiers.json` | Map small/medium/big → real models |\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/projects/<project>/` | Per-project run history, saved workflows |\\n\\nTrigger control: `/workflows-trigger on|off|status|set <word>`\\n\\n### Key APIs\\n\\n**Globals for workflow scripts:**\\n- `agent(prompt, opts)` — spawn subagent (tier, model, schema, isolation)\\n- `parallel(thunks)` — concurrent fan-out\\n- `pipeline(items, ...stages)` — sequential stages\\n- `phase(title, {budget?})` — group agents, optional token cap\\n- `checkpoint(prompt, opts)` — human approval gate\\n- `budget` — `{total, spent(), remaining()}` real-time tracker\\n\\n**Built-in quality patterns:** `verify`, `judgePanel`, `loopUntilDry`, `completenessCheck`\\n\\n**Agent options:** `tier`, `model`, `agentType`, `isolation: \\\"worktree\\\"`, `schema`, `retries`, `label`, `phase`\\n\\n### Commands\\n```\\n/workflows                    interactive navigator\\n/workflows status <id>        watch live\\n/workflows save <name>        save as reusable command\\n/workflows run <prompt>       force from prompt\\n/workflows-trigger off|on     keyword control\\n/workflows-models             map tiers to models\\n/deep-research <question>     web research + cross-check\\n/adversarial-review <task>    skeptical review\\n/multi-perspective \\\"<topic>\\\"  multi-angle analysis\\n```\\n\\n### Pi integration\\n- Registered via `pi.extensions: [\\\"extensions/workflow.ts\\\"]` in package.json\\n- Adds `workflow` tool + slash commands to Pi\\n- Uses Pi sessions for subagent isolation\\n- Hooks Pi TUI for live progress panel\\n- Stores state in `~/.pi/workflows/` (not per-project `.pi/`)\\n- Respects Pi's model auth for provider routing\",\n  \"## Research Complete: pi-dynamic-workflows Ecosystem\\n\\n**Key Findings:**\\n\\n1. **pi-dynamic-workflows package** exists at `/home/yash/.dotfiles/pi/.pi/agent/npm/node_modules/@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows`\\n   - Version 2.9.0, MIT licensed\\n   - Claude Code–style dynamic workflows for Pi\\n   - npm: `@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows`\\n\\n2. **Core concept**: JavaScript orchestration scripts (`.dwf.ts`) that spawn subagents in parallel, keep intermediate results in script variables (not chat context), return only results.\\n\\n3. **Key APIs**:\\n   - `agent(prompt, opts)` - spawn isolated subagent\\n   - `parallel(thunks)` - run multiple agents concurrently\\n   - `pipeline(items, ...stages)` - multi-stage fan-out\\n   - `phase(title)` - group agents in live view\\n   - `verify/judgePanel/loopUntilDry/completenessCheck` - quality patterns\\n\\n4. **Agent options**:\\n   - `tier`: \\\"small\\\" | \\\"medium\\\" | \\\"big\\\" - model routing\\n   - `model`: exact provider/modelId\\n   - `agentType`: named definition from `.pi/agents/`\\n   - `isolation: \\\"worktree\\\"` - git worktree isolation\\n   - `schema`: JSON Schema for structured output\\n\\n5. **pi-crew dynamic workflows** also found at `/home/yash/.dotfiles/pi/.pi/agent/npm/node_modules/pi-crew/docs/dynamic-workflows.md`\\n   - Similar concept but part of pi-crew package\\n   - Uses `ctx.agent()`, `ctx.fanOut()`, `ctx.pipeline()`\\n\\n6. **Pi coding agent** has built-in workflow support via extensions (subagent example shows chained workflows)\\n\\n**Installation**: `pi install npm:@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows` then `/reload`\\n\\n**Commands**: `/workflows`, `/deep-research`, `/adversarial-review`, `/ultracode`, `/effort`\\n\\n**Storage**: `~/.pi/workflows/` (global), project-scoped under `~/.pi/workflows/projects/<project>/`\",\n  \"## Research Summary\\n\\n### GitNexus Skills\\n\\n`pi-gitnexus` (v0.6.4) has **5 skills** — all codebase analysis, zero workflow-related:\\n\\n| Skill | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `gitnexus-debugging` | Trace errors via `gitnexus_query` → `gitnexus_context` → source files |\\n| `gitnexus-exploring` | Codebase exploration via `gitnexus_list_repos` → `gitnexus_query` → `gitnexus_context` |\\n| `gitnexus-impact-analysis` | Blast radius via `gitnexus_impact` → `gitnexus_detect_changes` |\\n| `gitnexus-pr-review` | PR review combining impact + context |\\n| `gitnexus-refactoring` | Safe rename/extract/move using `gitnexus_rename` + Cypher |\\n\\n**No workflow-related skills in pi-gitnexus.** All use knowledge graph tools (`gitnexus_*`) for code analysis.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Dynamic Workflow Packages (installed)\\n\\nTwo packages provide dynamic workflow capabilities:\\n\\n**1. `@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows` (v2.9.0)**\\n- Provides `workflow` tool (JS sandbox with `agent()`/`parallel()`/`pipeline()`/`phase()`)\\n- Keywords: `workflow` or `workflows` in any message auto-arms workflow mode\\n- Commands: `/workflows`, `/deep-research`, `/adversarial-review`, `/ultracode`\\n- Settings: `~/.pi/workflows/settings.json` (keyword trigger, etc.)\\n- Extension: `extensions/workflow.ts`\\n- Journaled + replayable runs, per-agent model routing\\n\\n**2. `@mediadatafusion/pi-workflow-suite` (v0.0.23)**\\n- Structured orchestration: 4 modes (Idle, Standard, Plan, Mission)\\n- Role-specific model routing: planner, executor, reviewer, validator\\n- Config: `~/.pi/agent/workflow-settings.json`\\n- Skills: `codebase-discovery`, `find-skills`, `git-safe-summary`, `implementation-planning`, `project-rules-audit`, `safe-execution`, `validation-review`\\n- Extensions: `workflow-modes.ts` (1.48MB), `workflow-model-router.ts`, `workflow-state.ts`, `workflow-tool-guard.ts`, etc.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Local Config Files\\n\\n| Path | Content |\\n|------|---------|\\n| `~/.pi/agent/workflow-settings.json` | Full workflow suite config (models, workflow gates, standard/plan/mission settings) |\\n| `~/.pi/agent/workflows/active.json` | Active workflow state: `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"idle\\\", \\\"updatedAt\\\": \\\"2026-06-30T17:13:33.976Z\\\"}` |\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/projects/` | Per-project workflow runs (current project: `pmigov-82340f88a085`, run: `mr0xqzdh-a8djmf`) |\\n| `~/.pi/agent/morph.json` | Morph plugin config (routing, stats, compaction) |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Key Takeaway\\n\\nDynamic workflows come from two **installed packages**, not from pi-gitnexus. pi-gitnexus is purely code graph analysis. The workflow tool in this session is powered by `@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows` (provides the `workflow` tool + `agent()`/`parallel()` API) and `@mediadatafusion/pi-workflow-suite` (adds structured modes, model routing, and plan/execute/review gates).\"\n]\n\nCreate a comprehensive but concise guide covering:\n1. What the plugin does (core purpose)\n2. How to install and configure it\n3. Key concepts (workflow file format, phases, agent(), parallel(), pipeline())\n4. How to write effective workflows — patterns and anti-patterns\n5. Common use cases with examples\n6. Tips for efficient usage\n7. Any gotchas or limitations found\n\nBe thorough but practical. Include code examples where helpful.",
