          "text": "{\"summary\":\"`@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows` is Pi extension for running Claude Code–style dynamic workflows: JavaScript orchestration scripts spawn isolated subagents, route them to model tiers, run them in parallel/pipelines, group work into phases, track tokens, resume/watch runs, and return compact results instead of dumping all intermediate context into chat.\",\"guide\":\"## 1. Core purpose\\n\\nUse plugin when task benefits from fan-out/fan-in:\\n\\n- parallel repo inspection\\n- multi-perspective review\\n- research + verification\\n- staged implementation planning\\n- adversarial review\\n- repeatable workflows saved as commands\\n\\nMain value: orchestration logic lives in script variables. Subagent chatter stays outside main chat context. Final result comes back small.\\n\\n## 2. Install + configure\\n\\nInstall:\\n\\n```bash\\npi install npm:@quintinshaw/pi-dynamic-workflows\\n```\\n\\nThen reload Pi:\\n\\n```text\\n/reload\\n```\\n\\nPackage registers extension like:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"pi\\\": {\\n    \\\"extensions\\\": [\\\"extensions/workflow.ts\\\"]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nImportant paths:\\n\\n| Path | Purpose |\\n|---|---|\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/settings.json` | global workflow settings, keyword trigger word |\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/model-tiers.json` | maps `small` / `medium` / `big` tiers to real models |\\n| `~/.pi/workflows/projects/<project>/` | per-project run history + saved workflows |\\n\\nUseful commands:\\n\\n```text\\n/workflows                       # interactive navigator\\n/workflows status <id>           # watch live run\\n/workflows save <name>           # save current/generated workflow\\n/workflows run <prompt>          # force workflow from prompt\\n/workflows-trigger on|off|status # keyword trigger control\\n/workflows-trigger set <word>    # custom keyword\\n/workflows-models                # configure tier -> model routing\\n/deep-research <question>        # built-in research workflow\\n/adversarial-review <task>       # skeptical review workflow\\n/multi-perspective \\\"<topi... [truncated]",
